modules.description: This module implements a Webmachine session manager that integrates with a custom backend for session storage and retrieval. It provides functions to create, fetch, update, and expire sessions using cookies for client-side identification, handling key validation, expiration, and data persistence. Concrete use cases include managing user authentication sessions, tracking client state across HTTP requests, and securely handling session data with configurable expiration and cookie attributes.

This module handles session management for web applications using Webmachine, providing functions to create, retrieve, and expire sessions based on HTTP requests and responses. It works with session identifiers, request and response objects, and time-based expiration logic. Concrete use cases include tracking user logins, maintaining shopping cart state, and managing CSRF tokens across requests.
